Chris is the one dynamic character in the bookâ€”he undergoes almost a complete transformation. Initially one of Fletcher's men, he begins escalating the situation with Shane. After Shane beats him up Shane makes a comment about Chris's goodness but of his immaturity as well. When Chris offers to take Shane's place at the Starrett's, we witness a man growing up and coming full circle. Chris is a character that is changed dynamically because of Shane.